name: BinExport 12 (Improved flow reconstruction)
body: New release binaries that address #99 and #100, which made the plugin much less useful with Binary Ninja.

name: BinExport 12 (for upcoming BinDiff 7)
body:
- IDA Pro: Build w/ IDA SDK 7.6
- IDA Pro: Fix empty input file hashes and filenames on IDA 7.5 and lower
- IDA Pro: Avoid dead-lock in logging code on IDA 7.5 and lower, use thread-safe alternative
- Ghidra: Skip functions in "non-loaded" address spaces
- Cleanup: Remove left-over SQL exporter code
- Reader class: `index`/`set_index` accessors for back-references in `Instruction`

name: BinExport 11 (for upcoming BinDiff 7)
body:
Binary Ninja:
- Compatible with all 2.3 releases: "stable", "dev" and "qt6-preview"
- macOS: Universal 2 Binary

name: BinExport 11 (for upcoming BinDiff 7)
body:
IDA Pro plugin:
- Built with IDA SDK 7.6 Beta
- macOS: Universal 2 binaries

name: BinExport 11 (for upcoming BinDiff 7)
body:
- Binary Ninja plugin for Windows, Linux and macOS
- Disable x86 NOP heuristic for non-returning functions with `-OBinExportX86NoReturnHeuristic:<TRUE|FALSE>`

name: Binary Ninja exporter MVP
body:
Merged #52.

Minimal first version for Binary Ninja that is somewhat usable.

Features:
- Logging
- Build address spaces and compute SHA256 of orignal file
- Gather entrypoints similar to IDA version of BinExport
- Write basic BinExport v2 proto with call and flow graphs nodes

name: BinExport 11
body: This is the version that ships with [BinDiff 6](https://www.zynamics.com/software.html) as per [release announcement](https://twitter.com/AdmVonSchneider/status/1234178304837668869).

name: BinExport 10
body:
This is the version that ships with [BinDiff 5](https://www.zynamics.com/bindiff/manual/index.html#NYYYY4), as per [release announcement](https://twitter.com/AdmVonSchneider/status/1105127771376963585)
- Port to IDA 7, with 64-bit builds
- Built on IDA SDK 7.2
- Export symbols and comments in the `binexport2.proto`
- Update dependencies
- Use standard C++ types

name: Build improvements and light refactorings
body:
- Let CMake handle all the external dependencies
- Some refactorings to bring the code more in line with the Google code style
- Code-signed the Windows binaries
